e effect that the section does not affect the responsibility of the Secretary of the Navy under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s732"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 732","children":[],"tail":" is omitted as unnecessary. The words “as may, in his judgment, be necessary” are omitted as surplusage. The words “members of the naval service” are substituted for “naval aviators” to avoid the implication that trainees are naval aviators while undergoing the training. The designation depends on successful completion of flight training."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab1559d6-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idab1559d7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 8217, added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/861/s1/164/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–861, § 1(164)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1515"},"text":"72 Stat. 1515","children":[],"tail":", related to authorized strength of Air Force in reserve commissioned officers in active status, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1662/a/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1662(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2988"},"text":"108 Stat. 2988","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12003"},"text":"section 12